 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  \colon  f\circ  f^{-1} = 1_{B}]]></fr:tex> be the counit of the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-000W.xml"
addr="erct-000W"
title="Inverse">inverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>. Given <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b:B]]></fr:tex>, we must show that the fiber of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001H.xml"
addr="erct-001H"
title="Contractible type">contractible</fr:link>; the centre of contraction is given by the pair 
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x, \epsilon  x\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
, and the required paths can be constructed via the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001R.xml"
addr="erct-001R"
title="Path object structure on fibers">univalence principle for fibers</fr:link> using the unit <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  f^{-1}\circ  f = 1_{A}]]></fr:tex>, the coherence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ \eta \sim \epsilon \circ  f]]></fr:tex>, and the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001V.xml"
addr="erct-001V"
title="Naturality of homotopies">naturality of homotopies</fr:link>.</fr:p>
